RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 14100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 9, 2022. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since December 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOSS BOSS gave chase through the backstretch and raced in range of the lead two deep on the turn, dug in past the eighth pole and got up later yards. STEVETHEVANDRIVER drew clear nearing the half mile pole and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole, raced off the rail on the turn and was caught in later yards. NO FOOLING DUDE chased, raced close off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the stretch. IMPETUOUS engaged in close early chase inside, raced at the rail on the turn then flattened leaving the eighth pole. WIZARD OF ODDS gave chase, raced in the three path of the turn and showed little in the lane. WIDGET FACTORY chased inside, rounded the turn at the rail and weakened in the lane. FIRST NAVY ADMIRAL came away rank, gave chase through the backstretch and rounded the turn in the five path.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 18500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KELSEY'S ANGEL rated close inside, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, took the nod two deep midway on the far turn and dug in determinedly to eke out the advantage over the game stretch effort of LINDA'S TAJ, who moved to the inside and rated the pace, cleared the challenge of Don't Annoy Me past the five sixteenths pole, was met at the rail midway through the far turn but dug in gamely to deep stretch before reluctantly ceding. DON'T ANNOY ME tapered in and stalked two deep, challenged approaching the three eighths pole but dropped back past the five sixteenths, raced in the three path on the far turn and flattened in the lane. RIA FORMOSA saved ground on the first turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. SWEET FACTOR saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn then flattened inside the eighth pole. WAY LUCKY showed little response through the backstretch. COASTING TO WIN stalked the early pace three wide then faded through the backstretch. AWESOME LUCKYCHARM hesitated leaving the gate, raced well back, was eased after a half mile and walked off post race.

ENTRY.OWNER: Burnsworth Richard and Metropolitan Thoroughbreds LLC
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,chased 3/8,nod 2d mid turn,determined effort lane

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside,pressured past 5/16,met mid turn,game try,relented

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Allowance Purse 30500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 9 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 9 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBA'S HAT TRICK took an immediate lead and rated the pace inside, was urged away at the rail on the far turn then kept alert through the stretch. O'RIGSBY saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase into the backstretch, raced in the three path on the far turn and came along for second mid-stretch. DUNCAN IDAHO stalked the earlier pace three wide, picked up the chase approaching the five sixteenths pole, raced two deep on the far turn then flattened the final sixteenth. HILLBILLY ROCK saved ground well off the pace, raced in the three path on the far turn and could only improve his position. MONKEY WRENCH showed little response through the backstretch. OFFICER STONE stalked two deep, challenged approaching the three eighths pole but dropped back toward the quarter, rounded the far turn near the rail and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Juba's Hat Trick
ENTRY.COMMENT: immediate lead,rated pace,urged away turn,kept alert lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEAP closed to the lead past the half mile pole and rated the pace, came under pressure leaving the five sixteenths, raced at the rail on the turn and held well under steady stretch handling. STORMIN' ANNA chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path and finished well while settling for second. GILDED QUEST gave chase, raced in the four path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. KIMSFAVORITESTORM chased, raced in the three path on the turn and flattened in the lane. FESSIN UP gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path and passed rivals in the lane. CLARIFICATION chased the leaders, rounded the turn in the three path and showed little in the stretch. SUPER WICKED chased through the backstretch and raced in the four path on the turn. KILLDRESS KAY chased inside, raced near the rail on the turn and weakened.

ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Richie Rich Racing Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 63. Claiming Purse 17500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,250 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances) NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEEMS TO WHISPER rated the pace inside, was met past the half mile pole and kept the edge over Bali Balifly leaving the seven sixteenths, drew clear at the rail midway on the far turn then kept alert through the stretch. SUPERSNAKE settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced close in the three path of the far turn but proved no match in the stretch. APPEALING ROAD saved ground on the first turn, gave chase leaving the half mile pole and entered the far turn near the rail, angled to the four path toward the head of the lane and finished evenly. HOV LANE became anxious in the gate and came away awkwardly, rated close inside on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail then flattened past the eighth pole. SHE'S MYBUDDYBUDDY raced well back inside on the first turn, gave chase past the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, was eased to the five path toward the head of the lane and showed little further. HOVEL raced well back toward the inside and showed little response through the backstretch. BALI BALIFLY stalked the early pace two deep, took a brief slim lead past the half mile pole and dueled from that point, but dropped back off the rail midway on the far turn and gave way. GRASS CUTTER stalked three wide, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but faded into the far turn.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 29400. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NAPA VALLEY took the lead between horses approaching the first turn and rated the pace, came under pressure nearing the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and held well under steady stretch handling. CAIRO BREEZE had a brief early lead then stalked at the rail on the opening turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and had to settle for second best. DIVINAS CONNECTION raced well back inside on the first turn, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the five path and came along for third inside the eighth pole. VOICE OF NOW stalked the early pace off the rail, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths then weakened in the lane. RUSH TO CANDY raced off the pace in the three path on the first turn, gave chase toward the three eighths pole but showed little response. PRINCE'S REWARD raced in the three path the first turn and showed little response through the backstretch. NICKANDME was reluctant to load then broke in the air and lost his rider at the break. The Stewards reviewed the start of this race before declaring it official.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 94. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. No n-winners Of A Race Since May 9 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since April 9 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAAGY saved ground on the opening turn then bid into the backstretch, was blocked in the four path through most of the far turn, altered course to the outside entering the stretch and dug in under steady handling to get up under the wire. JUNGLE BEAST settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole and raced in the six path on the far turn, took the nod leaving the turn and dug in under steady stretch encouragement, but was nipped under the wire. OVERLY CRITICAL raced in the three path the first turn, started a bid approaching the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn five wide, was bumped leaving the turn, lugged in across the path of Rad Paisley past the eighth pole, dueled to a brief slim lead past the eighth pole but was outfinished in the final strides. BRISTOL CHANNEL rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, was met a the rail past the quarter then flattened leaving the eighth pole. RAD PAISLEY settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn four wide, was forced outward and into Overly Critical leaving the turn, shut off past the eighth pole but came back to finish evenly. ALPHA CHI RHO stumbled to his nose and nearly lost his rider a stride out of the gate, saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then lacked a clear lane in the stretch. KOZY'S WILDCAT raced in the three and four paths the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the half mile pole, rounded the far turn three wide but drifted out and made contact with Rad Paisley leaving the turn and flattened stride in the stretch. TRINGALE raced with the pace two deep and between horses, challenged toward the three eighth pole, continued close through the far turn then gave way in the lane. After reviewing a claim of foul against the rider of Overly Critical for interference past the eighth pole, lodged by the rider of Rad Paisley, the Stewards disqualified the former to fifth place for interfering with the progress of the latter past the eighth pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIEUTENANT BROWN stalked from the two and three paths the first turn, took the lead three wide approaching the five sixteenths pole, dueled clear midway on the far turn and held on well with steady handling. REVEREND JACK had a brief early lead then stalked, started a bid toward the three eighths pole and challenged approaching the five sixteenths, but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and settled for second best. COMEONTURNMELOOSE was forced five wide into the first turn and settled off the pace, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. CRUISE ON BY drifted into the first turn and settled off the pace, picked up the chase leaving the turn, rounded the far turn about the five path then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. DON'T GET CAUGHTUP closed to the front approaching the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the half mile pole, was met toward the five sixteenths and flattened at the rail on the far turn. DISCREET LOVE came away awkwardly and dropped well back. REAL RICK was forced six wide into the first turn and never factored. Big Bad Brass ran loose in the post parade and was a late scratch.
